setup.explanation:
**Thanks for adding Member Counter to your server!**
__**Create/edit a counter**__
For this example we are gonna use `{members}`, which counts the total amount of members in your discord server, but you will find out more counters in the next pages
You can place that counter in one of the following places:

- In a **voice** channel **name**
- In a **category** channel **name**
- In a **text** channel **topic**
- In a **news** channel **topic**

Now create a new channel, edit it, and write `{members}` in the name or topic, and click 'save changes'

You can also add multiple counters in one name/topic, and combine them with your own content, here is a example:
```
{onlineMembers}/{members} Online Members, {youtubeSubscribers:https://www.youtube.com/user/enyay} Subscribers!
{onlineMembersWithRole:614777997291028519,614816383053856769} Admins and mods are online!
```

> If you reach the character limit when you are editing a name/topic, please check `{PREFIX}help editChannel`
> You can see the current counter configurations with `{PREFIX}seeSettings`, this is useful to add more counters without disabling the previous ones

__**Remove a counter**__
In a voice/category channel name:
Edit the channel name and write `{disable}` in the name, Member Counter will replace it a `‚úî`, that means that you removed all the counters of that channel successfully

In a text/news channel topic:
Just remove the whole topic.

You can also delete the channel directly
setup.counters:
__**Counters**__
> You should enable the the developer mode in Discord (User Settings > Appearence > Advanced > Developer Mode)
> To get an ID, right click in a channel/role and click "Copy ID"

> Those counters with an atherisk (\*) are premium counters, get more info in `{PREFIX}help upgradeServer`
> Counters with a cross (\‚ùå) are not available or implemented

- `{members}` Members in your server
* `{onlineMembers}` Online members in your server
* `{offlineMembers}` Offline members in your server
* `{users}` Users in your server (excludes bot)
* `{onlineUsers}` Online users in your server (excludes bot)
* `{offlineUsers}` Offline users in your server (excludes bot)
* `{bots}` Bots in your server (excludes normal users)
* `{onlineBots}` Online bots in your server (excludes normal users)
* `{offlineBots}` Offline bots in your server (excludes normal users)
- `{roles}` Roles in your server
- `{channels}` Roles in your server (excludes category channels)
* `{membersWithRole:role1ID,role2ID}` This counts how much members has a role or roles, write the roles IDs you wanna count after the `:`, and separate the role IDs with commas `,`
* `{onlineMembersWithRole:role1ID,role2ID}` Like `{membersWithRole:}` but only counts those members online
* `{offlineMembersWithRole:role1ID,role2ID}` Like `{membersWithRole:}` but only counts those members offline
* `{connectedMembers}` Total amount of connected members in the voice channels
- `{bannedMembers}` Amount of banned members in your server, the bot must have ban permissons to display this count
- `{http:url}` This will display the returned amount given by the response to the specified resource, the bot will perform a `GET` requeste and the server **must** reply with `the status code 200` and the `content-type: text/plain` return example: `{http:https://member-counter.eduardozgz.com/api/donation/count}`
- `{youtubeSubscribers:channelUrl}` Displays the youtube channel subscribers, replace channelUrl with the desired channel url
- `{youtubeViews:channelUrl}` Displays the youtube channel views
- `{twitchFollowers:channelName}` Displays the twitch channel followers, replace channelName with the desired channel name
- `{twitchViews:channelName}` Displays the twitch channel views

__**The following counters are of online players in a game server**__
Remember to replace `address` by the actual server address
\‚ùå `{minecraft:address}` Minecraft
\‚ùå `{terraria:address}` Terraria
\‚ùå `{rust:address}` Rust
\‚ùå `{cs:address}` Counter Strike: 1.6
\‚ùå `{css:address}` Counter Strike: Source
\‚ùå `{csgo:address}` Counter Strike: Global Offensive
\‚ùå `{tf2:address}` Team Fortress 2
\‚ùå `{gmod:address}` Garry's Mod
\‚ùå `{gtasa-mta:address}` Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas (Multi Theft Auto)
\‚ùå `{gtasa-mp:address}` Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas (SA-MP)
\‚ùå `{gta5-fivem:address}` Grand Theft Auto 5 (FiveM)

shortNumber.helpDescription:
This command allows you to show a count in a short form in counters placed in the name of a voice/category channel

**Usage**
```{PREFIX}shortNumber [enable/disable]```
**Examples**```{PREFIX}shortNumber enable
{PREFIX}shortNumber disable```
